# =============================================================================
# Trivy Ignore List — Azure Governance Platform
# =============================================================================
# Only CVEs with no available fix or in components outside our control.
# Review monthly and remove when patches become available.
# =============================================================================

# ecdsa 0.19.x — Minerva timing attack (CVE-2024-23342)
# Mitigated: ecdsa is only used by python-jose for JWT signing key parsing.
# Our JWT signing uses HS256 (HMAC/symmetric), not ECDSA curves.
# Azure AD token validation uses RS256 via JWKS, handled by python-jose's
# cryptography backend (not ecdsa). No ECDSA signing paths in our app.
# TODO: Migrate from python-jose to PyJWT to eliminate ecdsa dependency entirely.
CVE-2024-23342

# uv binary — container tooling only, not in app runtime path
CVE-2026-31812

# wheel/setuptools bundled deps — build-time only, not in runtime
CVE-2026-24049
CVE-2026-23949
